alert.note: Alert for San Luis Obispo (California) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Advisory issued January 05 at 3:17AM PST until January 05 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Oxnard
info.description: ...FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 615 AM PST THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected. * WHERE...A portion of southwest California, including the following county, Northwest San Luis Obispo County. * WHEN...Until 615 AM PST. * IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. Water over roadways. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 314 AM PST, Doppler radar indicated areas of locally heavy rain re-developing over the advisory area. Minor flooding is ongoing or expected to begin shortly. Between 0.5 and 1.5 inches of rain have fallen. - Additional rainfall amounts of 0.5 to 1 inch are expected over the area. This additional rain may result in minor flooding. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Paso Robles, Atascadero, Cambria, Lake Nacimiento, Cayucos, Templeton and San Miguel. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the dangers of flooding.
